heaviest_rainfall.status: 36.8mm of rain was recorded as having fallen on 04 January 2025, marking an exceptional 37.2 hour precipitation event.  At times the rain was falling at 4.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The rain rate reached 10.1mm per hour during the storm today (ranking 10th from our records) and resulted in 9.37mm of total rain in 16.6 hours.  27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: A storm today ranked 10th for the longest continuous rainfall according to our records, lasting a total of16.6 hours.  It came with 9.37mm of rainfall, at times, falling at 10.1mm per hour.  On 04 January 2025, the rain lasted for 37.2 hours, which is the longest time recorded by our database.  36.8mm accumulated and it fell at 4.6mm per hour at times.
